permanent_sub_1_Darknights_Memoir.name: Darknights Memoir
permanent_sub_1_Darknights_Memoir.detail:
This is the story of a mercenary, venturing through life and death on the battlefield.
This is the story of a follower, trusted by others yet failing to protect.
This is the story of a dissident, fighting endlessly, scorning life and death all the while.
This is the story of W, and her companions.

permanent_sub_2_A_Walk_In_The_Dust.name: A Walk in the Dust
permanent_sub_2_A_Walk_In_The_Dust.detail:
The extent of Kal'tsit's influence is immeasurable.
Ursus, Victoria, and Sargon all bear marks of her presence.
Whatever her role may be, she firmly and persistently pursues her own vision.
Those who journey alongside her, too, are busily authoring the stories of their own lives.
Time stops for no one, and Kal'tsit continues marching onward.

permanent_sub_3_Under_Tides.name: Under Tides
permanent_sub_3_Under_Tides.detail:
Skadi hears the trill of a long unheard melody at Rhodes Island.
Following the sound, she meets Gladiia.
Yet, this former comrade swiftly disappears after little more than a glimpse.
She kidnapped Specter, leaving nothing but a name for Skadi.
'Sal Viento', a lethargic and mysterious coastal town.
There, Skadi will unravel the mystery of her and her companions' bloodline.

permanent_sidestory_1_Grani_And_The_Trea.name: Grani and the Knights' Treasure
permanent_sidestory_1_Grani_And_The_Trea.detail:
Dewville, a remote village in Kazimierz has been occupied by bounty hunters.
These bounty hunters indiscriminately rampage and ruin, apparently in an attempt to find the knight's treasure said to be buried here.
After receiving a request for help, Mounted Police Grani volunteers to resolve the problem.
Can she really drive out the bounty hunters?
Will she find the mysterious knight's treasure?
Will peace return to Dewville?
Let's find it out.

permanent_sidestory_2_Heart_Of_Surging_F.name: Heart of Surging Flame
permanent_sidestory_2_Heart_Of_Surging_F.detail:
The Obsidian Festival is in full swing in the town of Siesta!
The Operators of Rhodes Island have come for a vacation as well.
Not before long, they learned that the eruption of a nearby volcano is imminent!
But it seems the town's government is trying to cover it up?!
In the midst of the summer heat, music and battle, 
Rhodes Island will set out with the mayor's daughter, Ceylon.
Will they manage to save the day?

permanent_sidestory_3_Code_Of_Brawl.name: Code of Brawl
permanent_sidestory_3_Code_Of_Brawl.detail:
Bison of MountainDash Logistics was ambushed and is hanging on for dear life?
His saviors are not his father's men, but Penguin Logistics?
It's Sauin, yet the darker undercurrents of Lungmen are out in force?
Who is the actual underground mastermind of Lungmen?
MountainDash Logistics? Penguin Logistics? The Siracusan Mafia? Or someone else?
In the dark of the night, an unmissable feast is about to begin!

permanent_sidestory_4_Twilight_Of_Wolumo.name: Twilight of Wolumonde
permanent_sidestory_4_Twilight_Of_Wolumo.detail:
Folinic and Suzuran arrive at this place, searching for the missing Atro.
Wolumonde, 'The Eighth Moon' of the Leithanien's Winterwisp Mountains.
Under the threat of Catastrophes, the town remains still while suspicion lurks in the people's eyes.
A great fire extinguishes many lives, but from the ashes more questions rise.
With the arrival of Reunion, the conflict between the Infected and the townsfolk reaches a climax.
Will this incident be resolved? Will there be answers to the mystery?
Please investigate the truth hidden in the twilight, alongside the operators of Rhodes Island.

permanent_sidestory_5_The_Great_Chief_Re.name: The Great Chief Returns
permanent_sidestory_5_The_Great_Chief_Re.detail:
The doctor, Gavial, and co. travel to Gavial's hometown on a low-altitude aircraft.
Acahualla, a place of lush forests within Sargon.
Close to their destination, the aircraft is struck down!
The doctor and Gavial have no choice but to travel on foot to the settlements to seek help.
What plots and threats do the vast rainforests hide?
Will the Rhodes Island operators be able to repair their aircraft and return?
Gavial, this is your home turf. It's all on you now!

title: How Stars Are Calculated
Operator's Personal Letter
Furniture Pack
desc: Once <color=#0098dc>Record Restoration</color> has become available, the player may attempt the corresponding Event Stages (excluding Story and Training stages). The number of Stars obtained in ratings will be counted towards your total number of Stars. They can be exchanged for <color=#0098dc>Record Restoration</color>'s corresponding rewards.

Raises a specific Operator to Max Potential. Meanwhile, <color=#cc3030>all</color> of the Operator's Tokens will be turned in (used).
If the Operator is already at Max Potential, the Operator's Personal Letter will be opened (used) automatically and the Operator's Tokens <color=#cc3030>will not</color> be turned in (used).

Includes all of the corresponding event's limited Furniture items (excluding purchasable pieces). If all the furniture pieces have been obtained, they may not be obtained again via <color=#0098dc>Record Restoration</color>.

sub_04-1-1.name: Cluster-1
sub_04-1-1.description:
Make good use of the Active Originium in the middle of the battlefield and things will be much easier.
<@lv.item><Active Originium></>Operators deployed on it and enemies who have passed it will take constant damage, but their ATK and Attack Speed will be increased significantly

sub_04-1-2.name: Cluster-2
sub_04-1-2.description:
Enemies are coming from more directions. Still it's recommended to build your defense around the Active Originium.
<@lv.item><Active Originium></>Operators deployed on it and enemies who have passed it will take constant damage, but their ATK and Attack Speed will be increased significantly

sub_04-1-3.name: Cluster-3
sub_04-1-3.description:
The alien force has split into two. It may be a good choice to consume their HP by the Active Originium.
<@lv.item><Active Originium></>Operators deployed on it and enemies who have passed it will take constant damage, but their ATK and Attack Speed will be increased significantly

sub_04-2-1.name: Myriapoda-1
sub_04-2-1.description: Please be careful of the Originium Slugs in the south and the north and don't let them go through our defense.

sub_04-2-2.name: Myriapoda-2
sub_04-2-2.description: The battlefield is narrow this time. Please think carefully about where to deploy Operators.

sub_04-2-3.name: Myriapoda-3
sub_04-2-3.description: The battlefield is even narrower. It's recommended to upgrade Operators to get through it.

sub_04-3-1.name: Rage-1
sub_04-3-1.description: Please pay attention to the joint attack of enemy's Originium Slugs and alien elite Casters.

sub_04-3-2.name: Rage-2
sub_04-3-2.description: Scatter the Operators and use ranged Operators to take out the Originium Slugs from afar.

sub_04-3-3.name: Rage-3
sub_04-3-3.description: There is not much space for melee Operators this time. Try using Specialist Operators to cope with the tough enemies on the left.

sub_04-4-1.name: Stand Firm-1
sub_04-4-1.description: A large number of elite enemies have appeared. Please be careful.

sub_05-1-1.name: Entrenched-1
sub_05-1-1.description: The enemies continue their massed assault. Beware of the Wraiths sneaking in from above.

sub_05-1-2.name: Entrenched-2
sub_05-1-2.description: The situation in the field is getting more complicated. Carefully deploy melee Operators to stop the swarm of enemy Breakers.

sub_05-2-1.name: Biting Cold-1
sub_05-2-1.description: Well armored Frost Drones are causing havoc with our forces. Counter them with Caster Operators.

sub_05-2-2.name: Biting Cold-2
sub_05-2-2.description:
The enemy force is a mix of Arts Masters and Frost Drones making it increasingly difficult to handle. Make use of Sniper and Caster Operators and don't forget our Jammers! 
<@lv.item><Jammer></> can stop nearby enemy drones from firing, greatly reduce their speed, and prevent them from activating special abilities after being deployed.

sub_05-3-1.name: Panic-1
sub_05-3-1.description:
Possessed Soldier Leaders can regenerate faster and pose a serious threat. Take them out first. 
<@lv.item><Turrets></> periodically fire bolts, dealing Physical damage to our units.

sub_05-3-2.name: Panic-2
sub_05-3-2.description:
Defense Crushers are enemy elite units specialized in defense. Their attacks can also stun our melee units. Take advantage of their slow moving speed to counter them. 
<@lv.item><Turrets></> periodically fire bolts, dealing Physical damage to our units.

sub_05-4-1.name: Hover-1
sub_05-4-1.description:
A large number of unmanned enemy drones have appeared on this operation. Please take charge of the anti-air defense.
<@lv.item><Jammer></> Stops nearby enemy drones from firing, greatly reduces their speed, and prevents them from activating special abilities.

sub_05-4-2.name: Hover-2
sub_05-4-2.description: Enemies attack from different directions in this battle. Be careful of the large number of Casters that are approaching.

sub_05-4-3.name: Abnormality-1
sub_05-4-3.description: A number of possessed enemies have appeared during this battle. Please make sure to fortify your defenses.

sub_06-1-1.name: Condensation-1
sub_06-1-1.description: The Yeti Squadron is utilizing Infused Glacial Originium Slugs in their assault upon us. Please be careful of these aberrant creatures.

sub_06-1-2.name: Condensation-2
sub_06-1-2.description: A failure to handle the synergy between Infused Glacial Originium Slugs and Icecleavers will result in massive losses.

sub_06-2-1.name: Hoarfrost-1
sub_06-2-1.description: An attack from a large number of Infused Glacial Originium Slugs, followed by a wave of Icecleavers, will inflict catastrophic damage to insufficiently prepared squads.

sub_06-2-2.name: Hoarfrost-2
sub_06-2-2.description:
Surrounded by a harsh environment filled with Originium Ice Crystals and powerful Icecleavers, how are we to mount a response to this attack? 
<@lv.item><Originium Ice Crystal></>Periodically releases a frigid wave that will inflict Cold to affected allied units.

sub_07-1-1.name: Ambush-1
sub_07-1-1.description:
Make good use of neural interference landmines to deal with guerillas that are difficult to injure through normal means.
<@lv.item><Interference Mine></>Upon explosion, deals heavy damage to enemies in the surrounding tiles and amplifies the damage they take for 15 seconds.

sub_07-1-2.name: Ambush-2
sub_07-1-2.description:
Use interference mines to establish a defensive line, expand our advantages, and accomplish our strategic goals.
<@lv.item><Interference Mine></>Upon explosion, deals heavy damage to enemies in the surrounding tiles and amplifies the damage they take for 15 seconds.

hard_05-01.name: Operation Inferno-1
hard_05-01.description:
The enemy is attacking with the full force of their drone armada! Proper use of Snipers and Casters is the key to victory. 
<@lv.item><Jammer></> can stop nearby enemy drones from firing, greatly reduce their speed, and prevent them from activating special abilities after being deployed.

hard_05-02.name: Operation Inferno-2
hard_05-02.description: The terrain on this battlefield is relatively simple, but beware of enemy Casters. Consider deploying units with high Arts Res to draw their fire or take advantage of the holes on the ground.

hard_05-03.name: Operation Inferno-3
hard_05-03.description:
The battlefield is full of winding roads and blanketed in a poisonous haze. These factors have greatly hindered our ranged Operators' effectiveness. Consider deploying more Medic Operators maintain consistent healing. 
<@lv.item><Poison Haze></> Operators lose HP constantly

hard_05-04.name: Operation Inferno-4
hard_05-04.description:
Faust has returned even stronger than before, and all Turrets on the field have been greatly enhanced. Plan your deployment positions and operators carefully to repel Faust's ferocious attack! 
<@lv.item><Turrets></> periodically fire bolts, dealing Physical damage to our units.

<@lv.rem><Special Conditions></> DP will not regenerate naturally.

camp_02.name: Lungmen Outskirts
camp_02.description:

<@lv.rem><Special Conditions></> DP will not regenerate naturally.

camp_03.name: Lungmen Downtown
camp_03.description:
Annihilate the Reunion armed forces that have invaded Lungmen, and regain initiative within the region.
<@lv.rem><Special Conditions></> DP will not regenerate naturally.

camp_r_01.name: The Grand Knight Territory Outskirts
camp_r_01.description:
A large-scale competitive exhibition game organized by the Kazimierz General Chamber of Commerce. As a defender, Rhodes Island must make use of sponsor drones to deal with the Knightclubs' elites.
<@lv.rem><Special Conditions></> DP will not regenerate naturally.

camp_r_02.name: Frozen Abandoned City
camp_r_02.description:
Well-organized Reunion guerrillas are hiding in this abandoned nomadic city in the tundra of Ursus. Be prepared for the deathly chill, as that is your only hope for victory.
<@lv.rem><Special Conditions></> DP will not regenerate naturally.

camp_r_03.name: Abandoned Mine
camp_r_03.description:
A remote mine in Ursus where the Infected Patrol Unit are hunting down the Infected. Make good use of the tricky terrain to buy time for the Infected to escape.
<@lv.rem><Special Conditions></> DP will not regenerate naturally and failing to save an Ursus civilian will result in a penalty of -1 annihilation count.

camp_r_04.name: Flooded Seashore
camp_r_04.description:
An unassuming beach on the coastline of Siesta currently overrun by Sicilians and rioters. Utilize the Command Terminals provided by the city of Siesta and apprehend them posthaste.
<@lv.rem><Special Conditions></> DP will not regenerate naturally.

camp_r_05.name: Watery Tidehollow
camp_r_05.description:
As the tides surge, the Seaborn grow restless deep within a vast cavern. With the help of the remaining Iberian machines there, eliminate the Seaborn threat once and for all.
<@lv.rem><Special Conditions></> DP will not regenerate naturally

camp_r_06.name: Long Spring Wastes
camp_r_06.description:

tile_volcano.name: Heat Pump Passage
tile_volcano.description: Pumps out high temperature gas periodically, dealing damage that ignores DEF and Art Res to any units on it.

tile_volspread.description: Spray out lava periodically, dealing massive damage to friendly units on the surrounding 8 tiles and melting down Roadblocks.

tile_wall.name: High Ground
tile_wall.description: Can deploy ranged unit on it. Impassable

tile_defbreak.name: Corrosive Ground
tile_defbreak.description: Reduces DEF by half of the Operator on it.

tile_smog.name: Exhaust Grille
tile_smog.description: The Operator on it will not be targeted by enemy ranged attacks.

tile_yinyang_road.name: Mark of Hui and Ming

tile_yinyang_switch.name: Mark of Dusk and Dawn

tile_poison.name: Gas Spray

tile_deepsea.name: Deep Water Zone
tile_deepsea.description: Enemies have reduced ATK and Movement Speed and continually lose HP when within
